            "id": "https://pjcavan.github.io/gh-pages/expensive-lemonade.html",
            "url": "https://pjcavan.github.io/gh-pages/expensive-lemonade.html",
            "title": "Expensive Lemonade",
            "summary": " Let’s say you run a lemonade stand where you usually sell a cup for $1. A grandparent pays you a year in advance for one lemonade per week, whether or not they turn up, at 80c each. You get a check for $41.60 -&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<figure class=\"post__image post__image--center\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://pjcavan.github.io/gh-pages/media/posts/1/Lemonade.jpeg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 48em) 100vw, 768px\" srcset=\"https://pjcavan.github.io/gh-pages/media/posts/1/responsive/Lemonade-xs.jpeg 300w ,https://pjcavan.github.io/gh-pages/media/posts/1/responsive/Lemonade-sm.jpeg 480w ,https://pjcavan.github.io/gh-pages/media/posts/1/responsive/Lemonade-md.jpeg 768w ,https://pjcavan.github.io/gh-pages/media/posts/1/responsive/Lemonade-lg.jpeg 1024w ,https://pjcavan.github.io/gh-pages/media/posts/1/responsive/Lemonade-xl.jpeg 1360w ,https://pjcavan.github.io/gh-pages/media/posts/1/responsive/Lemonade-2xl.jpeg 1600w\"  alt=\"glass of lemonade\" width=\"3375\" height=\"2250\"></figure>\n<p>Let’s say you run a lemonade stand where you usually sell a cup for $1.</p>\n<p>A grandparent pays you a year in advance for one lemonade per week, whether or not they turn up, at 80c each. You get a check for $41.60 - you’re happy.</p>\n<p>There’s a drought and you’re the only drinks seller in the area. You sell for $5/cup that week. Some people grumble that it’s expensive but buy it anyway. When your grandparent turns up, they’re still getting their cup for the 80c they already paid.</p>\n<p>After the drought ends, your HOA says that selling at $5 was unfair so you must reprice to $2 - you have to give $3 back to everybody you sold at $5 to. If someone knew you sold 100 cups that week, they could say $300 would be returned to customers. Imagine the headlines in the neighbourhood newspaper - “lemonade stand must fix $300 pricing error!” How embarrasing.</p>\n<p>But, $300 won’t be returned. Your grandparent bought at 80c - there’s nothing to return to them. If you had lots of those deals, the total returned might be far, far less than $300.</p>",
            "author": {
                "name": "Peter Cavan"
            },
            "tags": [
            ],
            "date_published": "2021-03-11T21:09:00-08:00",
